## Overview
Performed a full service version scan against Metasploitable 2 to map the attack surface.

## Target
192.168.56.101

## Tool
Nmap

## Command
```bash
nmap -sV 192.168.56.101
```

## Output Summary
20+ open ports including FTP (21), SSH (22), Telnet (23), 
HTTP (80), MySQL (3306), Samba (445), IRC (6667)

## Findings
Metasploitable runs dozens of outdated, vulnerable services 
exposed on the network with no firewall filtering.

## What I Learned
Always start with a full scan before attacking. Version 
detection (-sV) reveals exactly which exploits to use.
